Implemented and committed T-020.

Commit: `61548a9 feat(render): extract phrase features with partitura [T-020@20260416T181925Z]`

What changed:
- Added [features.py](/Users/anthony/Programming/PromptClaw/src/cypherclaw/render/features.py) with lazy `partitura.load_score` wrapping and phrase feature extraction.
- Computes `harmonic_charge`, `melodic_charge`, `metric_weight`, `is_cadential`, and `contour_apex`.
- Uses a normalized Lerdahl-style tonal pitch space/basic-space distance for `harmonic_charge`.
- Stamps feature metadata during score-tree to tracker compilation and propagates it onto tracker event steps.
- Added feature fields to `Event`; `FinalRitRule` now recognizes cadential metadata as well as the old phrase attribute.
- Added a MusicXML fixture and regression tests for stable known feature values.

Validation passed:
- `pip install -e '.[dev]'`
- `pytest tests/ -x --tb=short` -> `2860 passed`
- `ruff check src/ tests/`
- `mypy src/`

I left the pre-existing unrelated `progress.md`, `sdp/`, and `temp_artifacts/` workspace changes uncommitted.

Reference used for the Partitura API shape: https://partitura.readthedocs.io/en/stable/modules/partitura.html
